Executive Profile
Robert A. Heft Ph.D.Chief Executive Officer and Director, Alexion Montréal Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships62--
Background

		Dr. Robert A. Heft, PhD, serves as the Chief Executive Officer of ILIT BioVentures. Dr. Heft serves as Chief Executive Officer of Zingenix Ltd., a company focused on gene therapy for severe orphan disorders. Dr. Heft served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Alexion Montréal Corp. (Alternate Name: Enobia Pharmaceuticals, Inc.) from 2005 to 2012. He has over 30 years experience in the biopharmaceutical industry. He served as Vice President of Corporate Planning ... of BioMarin Pharmaceutical Inc. He served as Vice President of Product Development & Program Management of BioMarin Pharmaceutical Inc., since October 2002, having joined BioMarin in October 2001, when BioMarin acquired the pharmaceutical assets of IBEX Technologies, Inc. In January 1986, he founded IBEX and served as its President and Chief Scientist until 2001. While at IBEX, he directed the preclinical and clinical development of several enzymes for cardiovascular disease and metabolic disorders, was awarded several patents for work related to these enzymes and authored related papers. He held several senior positions with BioMarin Pharmaceutical Inc., Continental Pharma Cryosan, Inc. and IBEX Technologies, which he founded. He serves as Chairman of the Board of ELOXX Pharmaceuticals, Ltd. He has been an Independent Director of Ra Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since March 2016. He has been a Director at Clementia Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since June 2013. He serves as a Director of Lumos Pharma Inc., Zingenix Ltd., and VisionGate, Inc. He served as a Director of the Canadian Genetic Diseases Network and Alexion Montréal Corp. He served as a Director of BioCapital. He served as a Director of Ibex Technologies, Inc. from May 15, 2006 to December 14, 2010. He also serves on the Advisory Board of Sectoral Asset Management. He served as a Director of the Industrial Biotechnology Association of Canada. He was awarded several patents in the field of: coagulation, phenylketonuria and hypophosphatasia and has published in these fields. He has also received several awards for his work including: Company of the Year (Gold Leaf Award for Enobia Pharma) - 2012 BIOTECanada, Entrepreneur of the Year - Canada, 2012, Canadian Venture Capital Association, Genesis Award - 2012, from BioQuebec. Dr. Heft received a Bachelor of Mechanical Engineering from McGill University and a Masters degree in Nuclear Engineering from Cornell University before obtaining his PhD from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in Genetic Engineering/Radiological Sciences in 1986 and was a Neurology Fellow at the Massachusetts General Hospital.Read Full Background




